about.summary: MongoEngine is a Python Object-Document Mapper for working with MongoDB.

name: mongoengine
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "mongoengine" %}
{%set version = "0.10.6" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash_val = "007e3ac452c0a670e89c1d9755f7ddfc2f10982e6edda555e3671ee4cf7b12a5" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools

  run:
    - python
    - pymongo >=2.7.1

test:
  imports:
    - mongoengine
    - mongoengine.base
    - mongoengine.queryset

about:
  home: http://mongoengine.org/
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  license_family: MIT
  summary: 'MongoEngine is a Python Object-Document Mapper for working with MongoDB.'
  doc_url: https://mongoengine-odm.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/MongoEngine/mongoengine

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
